Windows Registry Editor Version 5.00

; Enable Focus Stealing in Windows using the ForegroundLockTimeout registry key
; This is a DWORD value that sets the time in milliseconds that a window must be 
; in the foreground before it can steal focus from other windows.
; The default value is 0x00000000 (0 milliseconds).

[HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Control Panel\Desktop]
"ForegroundLockTimeout"=dword:00000000